1.5
log
@Place SSL server certs in SYSCONFDIR/ssl not SYSCONFDIR/ssl/certs

To verify certificates, the OpenSSL default store is used, which
is (on MirOS) /etc/ssl/certs (not SYSCONFDIR); I think it's okay.

Bump patchlevel.
@
